President Correa also supported the decision to maintain Paraguay’s veto on membership in the Unasur Union at least until its next election, arguing that the whole “must be firm and not tolerate opportunism and coupism covered in legality” because in fact “it has destroyed the legitimacy of Paraguayan democracy.”
